def largestRectangleArea(heights):
    stack = []
    max_area = 0
    index = 0
    
    while index < len(heights):
        # Push index to stack if it's empty or current height >= stack top height
        if not stack or heights[index] >= heights[stack[-1]]:
            stack.append(index)
            index += 1
        else:
            # Pop the top and calculate area
            top = stack.pop()
            area = heights[top] * (index if not stack else index - stack[-1] - 1)
            max_area = max(max_area, area)
    
    # Calculate remaining areas for indices left in stack
    while stack:
        top = stack.pop()
        area = heights[top] * (index if not stack else index - stack[-1] - 1)
        max_area = max(max_area, area)
    
    return max_area
